# Collaboration & Firebase Rules

## Scope

Collaboration and Firebase code lives exclusively in `excalidraw-app/` — it must NOT be moved into published packages (`packages/*`). The core `@excalidraw/excalidraw` package must remain usable without any Firebase dependency.

## Real-time Sync

- Collaboration uses **Socket.io** for real-time element sync.
- Conflict resolution uses `reconcileElements()` from `packages/excalidraw/data/reconcile.ts` — do NOT write custom merge logic.
- Collaboration state (collaborators map, pointers) is part of `AppState` — update it through the standard state path, not directly.

## Encryption

- All data sent to the server is **end-to-end encrypted** — encryption/decryption happens client-side before any network call.
- Do NOT log, expose, or transmit decrypted element data outside the client.
- Encryption utilities are in `excalidraw-app/data/` — treat them as security-critical code.

## Firebase Security Rules

- Firestore and Storage rules live in `firebase-project/firestore.rules` and `firebase-project/storage.rules`.
- Changes to security rules require careful review — overly permissive rules expose user data.
- Test rule changes against Firebase emulator before deploying.
- Never deploy rule changes directly to production without review.

## Data Persistence Hierarchy

```
Local (IndexedDB / localStorage)   ← primary, always available
         ↓
Firebase Firestore/Storage         ← collaboration & sharing only
```

- Always write to local storage first.
- Firebase writes are best-effort for collaboration; local state is authoritative for the current session.
- Do NOT block the UI on Firebase operations.

## How to verify

- Test collaboration locally by opening two browser tabs and verifying real-time sync.
- Verify encryption: confirm no plaintext element data appears in Firestore documents or network payloads (use browser DevTools → Network tab).
- Firebase rules changes: run `firebase emulators:start` and test read/write scenarios before deploying.
- `yarn test:all` — must pass; collaboration unit tests live in `excalidraw-app/__tests__/`.
